<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1250">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–2545:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 1250<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">White
                                            House Map Room</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi>
                                        (<persName corresp="#p_HMGPJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top
                                        secret</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg?</hi></placeName>], <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-25">25 July
                                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>313. The President requests an immediate answer to White House
                                    message #311 (241035Z).<note n="1" xml:id="d1250fn1"><ref target="#d1246">Document No. 1246</ref>.</note> If an
                                    answer is not received within twenty-four hours, the
                                    proclamation will be released by the President and the Prime
                                    Minister. Please advise time of receipt of this message.</p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>